SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 798
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Zaydyn Anderson of
Greeneville High School on being named to the
TSWA Class 4A All-State football team.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Zaydyn Anderson of Greeneville High
School, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven himself a
formidable competitor on the football field; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Sports Writers Association (TSWA) recently named Zaydyn
Anderson to the 2025 Class 4A All-State football team as an athlete in recognition of his
excellence on the gridiron for Greeneville High School; and
WHEREAS, this honor represents Zaydyn's second All-State selection, as he was
named to the All-State team as a defensive back last season; and
WHEREAS, Zaydyn Anderson was also honored this season as Region 1-4A Co-Player
of the Year and was a semifinalist for the Class 4A Mr. Football award; and
WHEREAS, Zaydyn Anderson epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as
he has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off
the field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Anderson's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his family,
his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
SJR0798
011741
- 1 -

REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Zaydyn Anderson of
Greeneville High School on being named to the Tennessee Sports Writers Association's Class
4A All-State football team, wishing him much success and happiness in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
